  "source": "Corollary: \"Associativity and Commutativity of Multiplication\"\nof: \"Theorem 3.13 (Distributivity)\"\ngiven:\n. k, m, n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. \\product:of{\\product:of{k}:and{m}}:and{n} = \\product:of{k}:and{\\product:of{m}:and{n}}\n. \\product:of{m}:and{n} = \\product:of{n}:and{m}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Multiplication is associative and commutative: for all $k, m, n \\in \\omega$, $(k \\cdot m) \\cdot n = k \\cdot (m \\cdot n)$ and $m \\cdot n = n \\cdot m$. These follow from distributivity by induction.\"\nId: \"c1571597-e7ce-45b2-829e-88011eb561aa\"",
